Basic problems.

Make Description:
   Type "make" to compile the code.

All the features, 1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6, and 7, have been implemented.

The refraction feature only works for the user scence, so use -u to test.

Test Command:
1. Ray-sphere intersection and local reflectance.
   ./raycast [–u | –d] 0
2. Shadows.
   ./raycast [–u | –d] 0 +s
3. Reflections.
   ./raycast [–u | –d] step_max +s +l
   For example,
   ./raycast [–u | –d] 5 +s +l
4. Chess board.
   ./raycast [–u | –d] step_max +s +l +c
   For example,
   ./raycast [–u | –d] 5 +s +l +c
5. Refraction.
   ./raycast –u step_max +s +l +r +c
   For example,
   ./raycast –u 5 +s +l +r +c
6. Diffuse reflections using stochastic ray generation.
   ./raycast –u step_max +s +l +r +c +f
   For example,
   ./raycast –u 5 +s +l +r +c +f
7. Supersampling to reduce aliasing.
   ./raycast –u step_max +s +l +r +f +c +p
   For example,
   ./raycast –u 5 +s +l +r +f +c +p
